about.summary: Computes functional rarity indices as proposed by Violle et al. (2017) <doi:10.1016/j.tree.2017.02.002>. Various indices can be computed using both regional and local information. Functional Rarity combines both the functional aspect of rarity as well as the extent aspect of rarity. 'funrar' is presented in Grenié et al. (2017) <doi:10.1111/ddi.12629>.

name: r-funrar
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.4.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-funrar
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/funrar_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/funrar/funrar_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9137ebb5c5f1e76b4650fcd8172dc0a72d3b46eddd1235173449336b7661eb96

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cluster
    - r-dplyr >=0.4.3
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cluster
    - r-dplyr >=0.4.3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('funrar')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('funrar')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://rekyt.github.io/funrar/
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Computes functional rarity indices as proposed by Violle et al. (2017) <doi:10.1016/j.tree.2017.02.002>. Various indices can be computed using both regional
    and local information. Functional Rarity combines both the functional aspect of rarity as well as the extent aspect of rarity. 'funrar' is presented in Grenié
    et al. (2017) <doi:10.1111/ddi.12629>.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
